<UserId.>104203329072888201760< /UserId.><Text>I had an amazing experience with them very good customer service always answer my calls and questions !! Very professional  A very special thank you to Sonya for everything she has done< /Text><rate>5< /rate></record>

< Rating>
4</Rating>
< GmapID>
0x80dcdf1d3b2ac495:0xfe588c9adf68669e</GmapID>
<Pictures>None<//Pictures>< text>
I hired Oracle Law Firm after falling on a Big Budget film and was hurt and still hurt. My only issue is that I may have been unknowledgeable about where I could see a doctor as ALL of them refused me. I was overwhelmed with paperwork coming from the Workers Comp office and I was told that I didn't have to worry about that and the law office would handle it however I was not receiving medical treatment through workers comp and never got an answer on how to do so making me believe it was better to bare through the pain for the lawsuit and not charge up doctors bills. I was seeing my primary care doctor however those bills were not included in the case because I did not know any better.  I may have seen 4 doctors in 2 years and they were all doctors from the state.

Overall I know 1000% that my case was worth more than I received (I guess I should have called the office and asked more questions everyday being a pain in the butt for 2 years) however,  Suzy, the last Paralegal on my case, was very professional and caring in answering my questions and helping me after the case closed in getting at least what I thought I was agreeing to.

I think this is a great, reputable firm however be proactive in your case or you will lose out on money that should be for you to live more comfortable due to your accident! Do not sign anything without making sure you everything that is stated on the phone is either recorded or in print. Unfortunately due to the pandemic, I believe my case did not receive the attention that it should have nor were the medical records obtained as they should have been but I was afraid to not settle. Never settle anything in a rush!!!

I learned a lesson! Even when you hire a firm you still have to ask questions, demand care and make sure you speak with your paralegal and lawyer about everything involved in the case and make sure ALL of your complaints were taken care of and you visited ALL of the specialists that were ordered before you settle a case. I never saw a neurologist which was ordered and my nervous system is tremendously affected since then and part of that is not being able to focus and organize and understand what was happening. Once you settle there is nothing you can do about it except realize that you got royally screwed!

Hopefully this never happens again as this type of pain and the pain I will have for life as a result is not worth the settlement but if it did I would go back to Oracle but I would know to go to the doctor when I am in pain, don't force myself to go to work when I can barely breath from chest bruising for 3 months and report and record everything! If you do all of  the back end work yourself I think they will do the work in court but you will have to pay attention!! This is my first workers comp case so I don't have another firm to compare it to. I will refer them to family or friends and maybe they can be taken care of fairly knowing what I know now.<//text>
<UserId.>100057459765556834175< /UserId.><Resp>None< /Resp>< name>

I will say I appreciated them taking on my WC appeal.  However, once settlement talk seriously began and we were reaching the end,  I began to feel rushed.  End result after almost 1 year:  an agreement that left me nowhere close to whole, jobless, and without any future medical. I was encouraged by the Oracle attorney to sign as it was the best one could hope for.  Hindsight makes me think otherwise especially when I weigh in a few mistakes made along the way that should've never happened.  In fact, I brought them to their attention so I wonder about the firm's checks and balances. With it all over, I'm left with just a feeling of "being on the fence" with regard to my personal interactions with Oracle. Would I recommend them to friends/family? Probably not. Would I go out of my way to discourage one who had chosen them? No.  Good luck.< /Review>

**This is NOT a Positive Review**

I'm so very disappointed and feel what happened to me happens to customers more times than it should. And this kind of thing continues like some vicious circle. It's sickening. <userid>102518834151286326497< /userid><username>Roxanne Deason<//username><Date>1582046953779<//Date><rating>5< /rating>< Text>
I loved this little, hidden Gem. We had such a great experience. The food was fresh and the staff was friendly and helpful. If you're looking for a great Mongolian BBQ place that is close to Bakersfield; this is it. My husband was impressed with the selection of fresh ingredients and sauces available and I enjoyed the little extras that were included. We got there about half an hour before closing and Linda (our server) suggested we prep 2 bowls each so we wouldn't feel rushed before the grill closed. One bowl each was more than enough, but it was nice to have an extra to add just veggies. We will definitely be back.< /Text>

<userid>104651412981754995032<//userid>< Review>
The only Mongolian BBQ in the SCV area. It is a little restaurant and the sign outside is small so you could miss it. The food is good but not the best that I have had. The noodles are really orange as if they added food coloring. My daughter wouldn't even eat them and she loves noodles. The sauce mixture is different from other places I've been. I'm glad they added shrimp and keep it separate from the other meats. I wont say that is be a regular at this restaurant but it's a different change from all the chain restaurants and fast food joints.</Review>

<user>113895300689243855412<//user>< username>
Tony Chun< /username>
<Time>1551587896941</Time><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
Fantastic owners that provide excellent service, great quality to price AYCE Mongolian BBQ. If you're unsure, just ask for help or look at the recipe guide to come up with the flavor profile you want.

This is definitely a locals spot that most visitors would not find otherwise.

Is it a fine dining, white table cloth, Michelin star restaurant? No, not does it try to be. This is just good food at a good price for a family run business where the folks are really kind and have been an institution to this you're for a long time.

We love coming here as it never disappoints!< /review>

<pictures>None< /pictures>< UserId.>

<gmap_id>0x80c286c7265bbfbf:0x21e5950565941c7e< /gmap_id></record>
</dataset><record>
< Review>
I really enjoy eating here, it's an experience I take all my out of town guest there to share. To start you are offered bread or rice for the table, then there is a salad bar, a hot appetizers and soup options, then you have all the raw ingredients to create your own bowl, frozen shaved beef, pork, chicken or turkey, noodles and an array of veggies, then you go to the sauces, they have recipes posted so you know how much of each thing to add and the staff is always there to assist, then you take it to the chef manning the Mongolian BBQ, he dumps everything from your bowl and using a spatula chase's it around the BBQ, poor guy must walk miles a day. It cooks in no time. And comes off that grill steaming hot, smelling incredible, be warned it needs a few minutes to cool down,  before you get your first taste. Well worth the wait. Staff is attentive, food is fresh, great place for lunch, dinner or a party.<//Review>

< user_name>
Brian Bergstr√∂m<//user_name>
<review>This Mongolian BBQ is out of the way for me, but will stop there when ever we are nearby. I used to have an annual pass to Magic Mountain and my friends and I would always stop here and have dinner after.

It is not only Mongolian BBQ, they also have Chinese food buffet as well. I love the MBBQ, they have the sauces broken down to components, rather than simply choosing hot, medium or mild, you can choose the ingredients to make it HOT or mild. They also have more components and ingredients for the food as well. This is the only MBBQ I have been to that has peanuts and peppers.

I highly recommend this restaurant to everyone. But in my circles it is a bit off the beaten path.

UPDATE:
We ate here on a Magic Mountain trip about 2 weeks ago, and the food is still as amazing as my previous review and visits going back to the late 1980's.

They have remodeled in the time since my last visit and it looks much better, however they eliminated the Chinese food buffet, not that I ever ate off the buffet it was just kinda nice as an option.

Syd ruined her first bowl as it was way too salty, when we told the waiter he explained that this happens alot. People who visit other Mongolian BBQs will add too much of the sauces, reason being he told us, many of the other M-BBQs will water down the sauces so they last longer, which really doesn't make sense for them to do, as I simply use 15 ladle fulls of sauce rather than the 1 or 2 I need here.< /review>< rating>
5<//rating>
< resp>
None</resp>

While price wise this Valero is a good nickel or so higher than other Valeros in the area, this one has a decent car wash. If you have a Valero card, the price of their Ultimate Wash becomes only $3..and that's worth the extra nickel a gallon. Most gas stations with car washes charge up to $9-$10 for a similar wash.<//Review>

< rate>
1< /rate>
<Review>Summary: Because of the grand review on Yelp I decided to give Hi Tofu a try. This place was a little hard to find, it was tuck in the corner somewhat on the side of La Cocina Restaurant.

Foods: Korean Style Veggie Pancake, Hot Stone Bibimbap, and a spicy Seafood Soondubu (which according to Hi Tofu Menu is just: Tofu Soup).

The Veggie Pancake was very bland and oily, I don't understand how the reviewer speak so highly of it. The sauce for the Bibimbap was a non spicy flavorless paste and anyone with experiences should know that the sauce is the main ingredient which completes the Bibimbap dish. As for the Soondubu (or Tofu Soup), I was devastated. The silken tofu was completely unseasoned and uncooked, which is... unacceptable. And why were there jalapenos in my Soondubu? If you call this place you run authentic then you shouldn't be adding JALAPENOS.

Service: The old lady (whom I assume is the owner/relative) was very kind at first but became hostile when I told her how the cook should use less oil for the pancake, jalapeno should not be in the soondubu, and the kimchi should be fermented a bit longer.

Overall: Maybe, just maybe when I can no longer drive myself to Korea Town in Orange County, I'll give this place another try. But for now, I'll stick with Kaju in Garden Grove as my go to authentic korean food.< /Review>< Pictures>
None<//Pictures>

<date>1489484109253</date><Rating>4</Rating>< text>
Great quality bagels and bagel sandwiches. Perfect for lunch dinner or snack.
The potato bagel is the best!!!
I came in for 2 toasted bagels at 2:30 in the afternoon. The staff seemed like they were done with the day and not helpful. As I was there I saw that was not totally the case. The girl behind the counter gave a man his bagel sandwich and apologized  for the length of his wait. She offered him a muffin of his choice to make up for it. That was nice to witness. My bagels were as requested and delicious. I did not have a long wait.

< text>
During the pandemic, this location of Einstein's Bagels deserves a Gold Star.  The employees deserve an A+ for operating safely and following measures to keep us customers safe.  In fact I say it is the safest eating establishment in San Diego.  They are patient with me when I call after using the app which is not perfect, to adjust my order. Every time I place an order whether for pick-up or curbside, my order is ready within minutes.  Plus they do a great job making bagel sandwiches and my ice coffee. If you are looking for a quick breakfast, coffee or snack in a safe location, this place is the best.<//text>

< review>
Got our order in timely fashion, however... My potatoes were only add bacon / cheese, and there was sour cream slathered on top. My girlfriend's meal was supposed to be without lettuce, though it had plenty as you see in the photo. I was supposed to get tartar sauce for the shrimp, that didn't happen either. The cheesy broccoli, wasn't cheesy at all, maybe a pinch of shredded cheese on 2 of them. However, the zombie drink, and the red Dracula drink were both very good! The steak I ordered was cooked perfectly (for once), and the shrimp were also very good, though lacking tartar that was ordered. If it wasn't for the drinks and perfect steak / shrimp, this would be a 1 star review. (Yes I should of checked my order, but all this covid BS they were getting people in and out and I was trying not to hold up the line, next time I will make everyone else wait, lesson learned)< /review>

<user>102651684007308117541<//user><username>Lifestyle Collective</username><Date>1522272708105<//Date><rating>1< /rating><text>If there was a way to give negative stars, I'd completely rate this establishment with a negative 5 star rating. Where do I begin, is it the badly over prepared chicken tenders my son had, which nearly chipped his tooth (exaggerating, but nevertheless that's how over cooked they were) or is it the microwaved french fries that were deep fried to hide their freezer burned taste. It quite possibly could have been the wanna be latin hipster model bartender who thinks he's a tough guy for talking down at a customer who simple was asking for a drink the server had yet to bring after 20mins of waiting (not over exaggerating that part, bartender nor wait).

I find it very disappointing that this Applebee's was very unprepared as a staff and operating business. The kitchen made several mistakes throughout our order and just sitting at our booth observing the room, it seemed to be, we weren't the only group who had a lack luster experience.

Fortunately, the manager and our server had some decency about them and attempted to correct the issue. However, that time came and went with Mr tough guy at the bar. They did decide to comp the chicken fingers and drink, which was considerate of them. But, by far, the reputation and experience had already been damaged.

If you happen to find yourself at this location, tred carefully at the bar, confrontational wannabe model may try to spike your drink or may just have you waiting aimlessly. If you dare choose to sit, beware of the teeth chipping chicken fingers and long delays with a lost staff who jist may need an overhual in efficiency... probably starting with the kitchen.

<review>If there was a way to give negative stars, I'd completely rate this establishment with a negative 5 star rating. Where do I begin, is it the badly over prepared chicken tenders my son had, which nearly chipped his tooth (exaggerating, but nevertheless that's how over cooked they were) or is it the microwaved french fries that were deep fried to hide their freezer burned taste. It quite possibly could have been the wanna be latin hipster model bartender who thinks he's a tough guy for talking down at a customer who simple was asking for a drink the server had yet to bring after 20mins of waiting (not over exaggerating that part, bartender nor wait).

I find it very disappointing that this Applebee's was very unprepared as a staff and operating business. The kitchen made several mistakes throughout our order and just sitting at our booth observing the room, it seemed to be, we weren't the only group who had a lack luster experience.

Fortunately, the manager and our server had some decency about them and attempted to correct the issue. However, that time came and went with Mr tough guy at the bar. They did decide to comp the chicken fingers and drink, which was considerate of them. But, by far, the reputation and experience had already been damaged.

If you happen to find yourself at this location, tred carefully at the bar, confrontational wannabe model may try to spike your drink or may just have you waiting aimlessly. If you dare choose to sit, beware of the teeth chipping chicken fingers and long delays with a lost staff who jist may need an overhual in efficiency... probably starting with the kitchen.

So... all in all, Applebee's never go back... not worth the unfulfilled hunger and hassle. Hopefully this helps someone before it's too late!<//review><Rate>1<//Rate>< UserId.>

< userid>
114253389029602100240<//userid>
<user_name>Ann's Simply Delicious Recipes<//user_name><Date>1409905836707</Date>< rate>
5<//rate>
< Text>
This review is long overdue, sorry about that!
On August 17th, 2014, my Honey and I set out for an early dinner. My appetite was leaning towards Applebee‚Äôs.

I had informed my husband that they had added some healthy choices to their menu since the last time we made a visit. Early this year we were unable to stay and dine because there were no choices of interest for him. So I was pretty sure that this time he would find something.

The host greeted us in a timely fashion. I asked the greeter if my husband could please view one of the menus before seating us, and that was no problem.
He did find a few things to his amazement.

We were escorted to a nice area of the restaurant, and quickly greeted by our wait.
A very cheerful young man approached our table and introduced himself as Robert. I have to say that his eagerness made me feel good and put a big smile on my face! I love it when waits are so cheery-eerie. We had a few questions regarding one of the entrees, so Robert took the initiative to go and ask one of his managers to come over and speak with us.

Within a minute we were greeted by Brittany, who had a bubbly outgoing personality. She explained that however, we wanted to substitute rice for more vegetables or another selection that they do their best to accommodate their customers. Their aim is to make sure that customers have a good experience and return.

My husband made a special request for more veggies in place of rice with his entree. Robert placed our order, and shortly after he walked away another manager approached our table and announced that the order would be coming right up; ‚ÄúIn fact sir, I will prepare it for you to make sure that it is just the way you like it!

Long story short, when Robert returned with the food everything was perfect. The veggies were crisp just as he likes them and the portion was huge. The grilled chicken was melt in your mouth and seasoned to perfection! I had the Bourbon steak and it was equally prepared to my liking.

I must say, the food was delicious and we were treated like royalty!
The staff is fantastic at this location. The two managers, Armando and Brittany go far beyond their call of duty to give the best in customer service. Our wait, Robert, was extremely accommodating, delightful and polite.

Thank you all for such an awesome experience. Corporate is most fortunate to have you as employees!  Keep up the great work!

Chef Ann<//Text>
